            <abstract id="ref65" label="Abstract">This collection contains the personal and professional papers of human rights attorney Peter Weiss (1925- ). Born in Austria in 1925, Weiss moved to the U.S. in 1941 and worked as a lawyer from 1955 to 2006. This collection contains materials related to Weiss's professional career and his involvement in human rights issues. Materials contained within this collection include notes, research materials, published and unpublished works created between 1963 and 1993, personal and professional correspondence written between the 1940s and the 1990s, travel itineraries, transcripts, and ephemera related to Weiss's numerous speaking engagements.</abstract>
            <langmaterial id="ref3" label="Language of Materials note">Most materials are in English. Other materials are in Spanish, French, and Italian.</langmaterial>
            <physloc id="ref73" label="Location note">Materials are located at the Tamiment Library.</physloc>
